The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 799) This DVD allows you to revisit some magic moments from the 

life of Louis Armstrong ? his upbringing in New Orleans to his journey as an actor, 

singer and musician. Lots of clips with Satchmo in performance as well. 

THE PHOTOS

 (Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, from August 13, 2 pm-7pm) The photographs 

by Tapomoy Guha Sarkar capture the moments and moods of 21 individuals living 

in Kalighat and in an all-girls shelter. 

THE DISPLAY

 (Artisana, 

August 8 to 15, 11 am to 7 pm) The exhibition, organised by Crafts Council of 

West Bengal, displays the crafts and textiles in styles developed by the Tagore 

family. There are saris from Sravasti using traditional embroideries. A special 

programme to mark Rabindranath Tagore?s death anniversary will be held on August 

8 at 11 am. 




